<!-- ==================== 1. VERDICT BANNER ==================== -->
<div id="verdict" class="card card-green verdict-banner green-banner">
  <h1>🏆 Migration Comparison Verdict</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">PatternFly 5 → 6 migration evaluation for <strong>forklift-console-plugin</strong></p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card score-card card-green">
      <div class="branch-name">pf-codemods-053026-2011</div>
      <div class="score" style="color: var(--green);">54</div>
      <div class="label">/ 100 — WINNER</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card score-card card-red">
      <div class="branch-name">semver/goose/053026-1839</div>
      <div class="score" style="color: var(--red);">38</div>
      <div class="label">/ 100</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top: 1rem;">Key Reasons</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Neither branch is merge-ready.</strong> Both fail the webpack build due to shared package.json issues, and both leave large portions of the PF6 migration incomplete.</li>
    <li><strong>Branch 1 wins on correctness:</strong> It introduces zero new TypeScript errors, makes only verified PF6-correct changes (ModalVariant → deprecated path), and has surgical scope discipline (23 files).</li>
    <li><strong>Branch 2 loses on correctness:</strong> Despite broader migration coverage (165 files), it introduces <span class="metric metric-red">88 incorrect <code>component=</code> prop misuses</span> that break UI rendering, <span class="metric metric-red">16 new TypeScript errors</span>, and <span class="metric metric-red">destructive package.json changes</span> (react-charts downgraded from 8.4.0→6.2.3, react-i18next from v11→v2.2.3, eslint range mangled).</li>
    <li><strong>Branch 1's main weakness</strong> is that it only addresses one migration area (ModalVariant deprecated imports) out of the dozens required. It's a correct but very small first step.</li>
    <li><strong>Branch 2's main weakness</strong> is that many of its changes are semantically wrong — especially the systematic pattern of moving children text into <code>component=</code> props, which would cause runtime breakage across the entire application.</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--orange);"><strong>⚠️ Recommendation:</strong> Use Branch 1 as the starting point. Cherry-pick the <em>correct</em> changes from Branch 2 (CSS pf-v5→pf-v6 renames, Icon wrapper removal, SelectList additions, test selector updates) after manual review. Discard Branch 2's package.json changes and component= prop misuses entirely.</p>
</div>

