<!-- Package Upgrades -->
<details>
  <summary>📦 Package Upgrades</summary>
  <div class="details-content">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PatternFly 6 requires specific package versions. The main branch already has correct PF6 versions: <code>@patternfly/react-core: 6.4.0</code>, <code>@patternfly/react-charts: 8.4.0</code>, <code>@patternfly/react-table: 6.4.0</code>, etc. The key chart package for PF6 is version 8.x (which includes the <code>/victory</code> subpath export).</p>

    <h4>Branch 1: pf-codemods-053026-2011</h4>
    <p><span class="badge badge-green">No package.json changes</span> — leaves the already-correct PF6 versions intact.</p>

    <h4>Branch 2: semver/goose/053026-1839</h4>
    <p><span class="badge badge-red">Destructive package.json changes</span></p>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Package</th><th>Main (correct)</th><th>Branch 2 (changed)</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
      <tr><td><code>@patternfly/react-charts</code></td><td>8.4.0</td><td>^6.2.3</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">WRONG — downgraded to PF5-era version</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>react</code></td><td>17.0.2</td><td>^18.3.1</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">WRONG — Console provides React 17</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>react-dom</code></td><td>17.0.2</td><td>^18.3.1</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">WRONG — must match Console host</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>react-i18next</code></td><td>^11.14.3</td><td>^2.2.3</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">WRONG — ancient version, types missing</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>react-router-dom</code></td><td>5.3.x</td><td>^7.16.0</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">WRONG — Console provides v5</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>eslint</code></td><td>^9.23.0</td><td>^3.0.0 || ^4... || ^8.0.0-0</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">WRONG — nonsensical range</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk</code></td><td>^4.20.0</td><td>^4.21.0</td><td><span class="badge badge-orange">Minor — acceptable</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>echarts</code></td><td>(not present)</td><td>^5.6.0 || ^6.0.0</td><td><span class="badge badge-orange">Added — unclear justification</span></td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>The react-charts downgrade from 8.4.0 to 6.2.3 is particularly damaging because version 8.x is the correct PF6-aligned version that provides the <code>/victory</code> subpath exports. Downgrading to 6.x causes the 4 <code>TS2307: Cannot find module '@patternfly/react-charts/victory'</code> errors.</p>

    <p><strong>Winner: <span class="badge badge-green">Branch 1</span></strong> — preserving correct versions is better than breaking them.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Modal Migration -->
<details>
  <summary>🔲 Modal / ModalVariant → Deprecated Path</summary>
  <div class="details-content">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>The old <code>Modal</code> API (with <code>title</code>, <code>actions</code> props) is deprecated. In PF6, <code>ModalVariant</code> should be imported from <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code> if still using the old API pattern. The new composable Modal (ModalHeader/ModalBody/ModalFooter children) is the promoted pattern.</p>
    <p>This codebase already uses the composable Modal pattern (ModalHeader, ModalBody, ModalFooter as children) but still imports <code>ModalVariant</code> from the main <code>@patternfly/react-core</code> export — which in PF6 refers to the <em>new</em> composable Modal, not the deprecated one.</p>

    <h4>Before (main branch)</h4>
    <pre><code>import { Form, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core';</code></pre>

    <h4>After (Branch 1 — correct)</h4>
    <pre><code>import { Form } from '@patternfly/react-core';
import { ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';</code></pre>

    <h4>Branch 2</h4>
    <p><span class="badge badge-red">No changes made</span> — ModalVariant remains imported from <code>@patternfly/react-core</code> in all 16+ files.</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Branch 1</th><th>Branch 2</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Files with ModalVariant → deprecated</td><td><span class="metric metric-green">21 files</span></td><td><span class="metric metric-red">0 files</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Remaining ModalVariant in main exports</td><td>0</td><td>16+</td></tr>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Winner: <span class="badge badge-green">Branch 1</span></strong> — this is the only migration area Branch 1 addresses, but it does it correctly and thoroughly.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Icon Component -->
<details>
  <summary>🎨 Icon Component Wrapper Removal</summary>
  <div class="details-content">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, the <code>&lt;Icon&gt;</code> wrapper component is still available but the pattern of wrapping individual icons in <code>&lt;Icon size="md"&gt;</code> is being replaced by passing icons directly via component props (like <code>icon={&lt;HelpIcon /&gt;}</code> on Button, or using the icon directly).</p>

    <h4>Branch 1</h4>
    <p><span class="badge badge-red">No changes</span> — 19 Icon wrapper usages remain (same as main).</p>

    <h4>Branch 2</h4>
    <p><span class="badge badge-green">Partially addressed</span> — reduced from 19 to 12 Icon wrappers. Changes include:</p>
    <pre><code>// Before (main)
&lt;Icon size="md"&gt;
  &lt;HelpIcon /&gt;
&lt;/Icon&gt;

// After (Branch 2) — Icon removed, used directly
&lt;HelpIcon /&gt;</code></pre>
    <p>Also correctly moved icon from children to <code>icon</code> prop on MenuToggle:</p>
    <pre><code>// Before
&lt;MenuToggle variant="plain"&gt;
  &lt;EllipsisVIcon /&gt;
&lt;/MenuToggle&gt;

// After (Branch 2)
&lt;MenuToggle variant="plain" icon={&lt;EllipsisVIcon /&gt;} /&gt;</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Removing <code>&lt;Icon size="md"&gt;</code> wrappers without replacing the sizing may cause visual regressions where icons were explicitly sized.</p>

    <p><strong>Winner: <span class="badge badge-orange">Branch 2</span></strong> — partial progress, but Icon sizing loss is a concern.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- SelectList -->
<details>
  <summary>📋 SelectList Wrapping</summary>
  <div class="details-content">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6's composable Select, <code>SelectOption</code> children should be wrapped in a <code>&lt;SelectList&gt;</code> component. This was already done in most of the codebase on main (111 existing references), but Branch 2 adds it to additional components that were missing it.</p>

    <h4>Branch 2 example:</h4>
    <pre><code>// Before (missing SelectList wrapper)
&lt;PfSelect ...&gt;
  {options.map(([key, value]) =&gt; (
    &lt;SelectOption key={key} value={key}&gt;{value}&lt;/SelectOption&gt;
  ))}
&lt;/PfSelect&gt;

// After (Branch 2 — correct)
&lt;PfSelect ...&gt;
  &lt;SelectList&gt;
    {options.map(([key, value]) =&gt; (
      &lt;SelectOption key={key} value={key}&gt;{value}&lt;/SelectOption&gt;
    ))}
  &lt;/SelectList&gt;
&lt;/PfSelect&gt;</code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Branch 1</th><th>Branch 2</th></tr>
      <tr><td>New SelectList wrapping added</td><td>0</td><td>~6 components</td></tr>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Winner: <span class="badge badge-orange">Branch 2</span></strong> — correctly applied pattern.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- InputGroupItem -->
<details>
  <summary>📥 InputGroupItem Wrapping</summary>
  <div class="details-content">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PF6 requires <code>InputGroup</code> children to be wrapped in <code>&lt;InputGroupItem&gt;</code>. This enforces consistent spacing and alignment.</p>

    <h4>Branch 2 example:</h4>
    <pre><code>// Before
&lt;InputGroup&gt;
  &lt;DatePicker value={date} ... /&gt;
&lt;/InputGroup&gt;

// After (Branch 2 — correct)
&lt;InputGroup&gt;
  &lt;InputGroupItem&gt;
    &lt;DatePicker value={date} ... /&gt;
  &lt;/InputGroupItem&gt;
&lt;/InputGroup&gt;</code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Branch 1</th><th>Branch 2</th></tr>
      <tr><td>InputGroupItem additions</td><td>0</td><td>26 references across date/search filters</td></tr>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Winner: <span class="badge badge-green">Branch 2</span></strong> — correctly applied PF6 pattern.</p>
  </div>
</details>

